descript.abstract: Business Improvement Districts (BIDs) are a type of assessment district in which business owners choose to be assessed a fee, which is collected on their behalf by the City, for use in promoting and improving the business area. In California, BIDs date back to 1965 with the approval of Assembly Bill 103 - the "Parking and Business Improvement Area Law." Today there are approximately 200 BIDs in the state.
descript.purpose: A BID provides a business area with the resources to develop marketing campaigns, increase awareness and lobbying efforts, secure additional funding and enhance public improvement and beautification projects in partnership with the City
